@startuml
!include _yunlink_protocol_theme.iuml
title Yunlink Test World Map - Failure Model

[*] --> ReceiveCommand

ReceiveCommand --> FailedSession : no active session
ReceiveCommand --> FailedTarget : wrong target / scope
ReceiveCommand --> FailedTtl : TTL expired
ReceiveCommand --> CheckAuthority : session + target fresh

CheckAuthority --> FailedAuthority : no authority / stale lease
CheckAuthority --> PublishRos : authority valid

PublishRos --> FailedPublish : ROS publish failed
PublishRos --> Accepted : publish ok

Accepted --> InProgress : FSM enters execution state
Accepted --> FailedTimeout : no progress before timeout

InProgress --> Succeeded : FSM converges
InProgress --> FailedTimeout : execution timeout
InProgress --> FailedSessionLost : session lost during execution
InProgress --> FailedAuthorityLost : authority lost during execution

FailedSession --> [*]
FailedTarget --> [*]
FailedTtl --> [*]
FailedAuthority --> [*]
FailedPublish --> [*]
FailedTimeout --> [*]
FailedSessionLost --> [*]
FailedAuthorityLost --> [*]
Succeeded --> [*]

state FailedSession <<Risk>>
state FailedTarget <<Risk>>
state FailedTtl <<Risk>>
state FailedAuthority <<Risk>>
state FailedPublish <<Risk>>
state FailedTimeout <<Risk>>
state FailedSessionLost <<Risk>>
state FailedAuthorityLost <<Risk>>
state Succeeded <<ActiveState>>
state Accepted <<Transit>>
state InProgress <<Transit>>

note right of PublishRos
Current tests cover mapping, loopback, and tracker logic.
Real Sunray/PX4 executor failures are still missing.
end note
@enduml

